---
description: Conventions for Eleventy posts under src/_posts (paths, front matter, drafts).
globs: ['src/_posts/**/*.md']
alwaysApply: false
---

## Paths and filenames

- Location: `src/_posts/YYYY/YYYY-MM-DD-kebab-slug.md`
- The folder **`YYYY`** must match the calendar year in **`date`** and in the filename prefix.

## Required front matter

- `layout: layouts/single_post.njk`
- `title`
- `date` — date-only `YYYY-MM-DD` (Los Angeles–aligned semantics per project docs) or full ISO with offset; must agree with the filename date
- `tags` — must include `post` (scalar `tags: post` or a YAML list)

## Drafts

- `draft: true` — excluded from **production** builds; still built in **dev** (`eleventy/config/preprocessors.js`).
- Remove `draft` or set `draft: false` when publishing; then run `pnpm run test frontmatter`.

## Optional / careful fields

- `description` — quote when it contains colons, quotes, or YAML-friction characters (`docs/authoring.md`, Frontmatter Formatting).
- `ogImage` — omit or rely on auto-generation unless setting a concrete path.
- `permalink` / URL changes — prefer `src/_data/redirects.yaml` for old URLs (`docs/authoring.md`, Redirects).

## Detail

See `docs/authoring.md` and `docs/templates/post-template.md` at the repository root.
